        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We have selected the TDM mode for all basebands since we only require continuum observations in this band and for this science goal.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We have selected an angular resolution of 0.1" to measure the continuum emission at comparable angular resolutions to that of our Band 9 observations (see Science Goal 3) as well as that of our soon to be obtained JVLA observations. This will allow us to compare the unresolved continuum emission and determine its spectral shape with less biases arising from measuring the continuum flux at different angular resolutions. The continuum emission is unresolved down to 0.3" in our Cycle 2 observations, so we do not expect to detect any extended structures that would require the ACA.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Extrapolating from our Cycle 2 continnum flux at 343 GHz, we expect the flux at 470 GHz to be ~ 1.5 mJy if the (sub-)mm continnum emission is dominated by thermal dust emission, and ~ 0.65 mJy if dominated by synchrotron emission. The requested RMS of 0.2 mJy/beam over a 7.5 GHz bandwidth allows us to detect the continuum flux at ~3sigma if the latter is true, and at &gt; 7sigma if the former is true, assuming the source is unresolved. 

</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>As we want to determine the spectral shape of the sub-mm continuum in our target, we want to obtain the continuum measurements at frequencies spaced as far apart as possible from each other. We already have Band 7 continuum measurements at 343 GHz from Cycle 2, and we are requesting the 676 GHz continuum as well in this proposal (Science Goal 3). The standard continuum frequencies in this band (Band 8), centered at 400 GHz, is too close to our Band 7 continuum measurements. Setting it to centre at 473 GHz is more beneficial for our goals. We have also tuned the basebands to coincide with frequency regions with the best possible atmospheric transmission given these constraints, and that have the least number of atmospheric absorption lines within the observing bands. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_NON_STD_CONT_FREQ</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
